[[File:Hypergate.png|thumb|right|250px|An active hypergate]]
{{Quote|As I understand it, a hypergate links two points in space instantaneously through a rift in hyperspace.|Colonel [[Jadick]]|<ref name="TOR">{{TORcite|type=faction|Republic|Ancient Allies|the ''Gav Daragon''}}</ref>}}
'''Hypergates''' were a form of faster-than-light transportation used by the ancient [[Gree (species)/Legends|Gree]] civilization.

==Overview==
Hypergates had a variety of sizes and functionality<ref name="TORC">{{TORcite|type=codex|Gree Hypergates}}</ref> with such shapes typically being freestanding accessways, gateways,<ref name="TGE">{{JournalCite|8|The Gree Enclave}}</ref> or archways. Those that activated the technology and stepped through the threshold were instantly transported through hyperspace to a corresponding hypergate<ref name="TORC" /> terminus at another location. Such locations tended to vary as a receiving hypergate was capable of being located on the planet of origin or another world entirely<ref name="TGE" /> with rumors of this latter fleet known of variant gates that were capable of sending entire starships across the galaxy.<ref name="TORC" />

They were considered a significant development of [[Gree technology]].<ref name="TGE" /> Amongst the Gree, the hypergates were venerated by their culture as sacred relics of technological works of art. Their civilization had long claimed that only the elite [[Gatemaster]]s of their Operator caste were capable of activating a hypergate, though this may have been a cultural bias.<ref name="TORC" /> They became a lost technology that the Gree refused to duplicate. One variant of these devices was the [[Grand Hypergate]].<ref name="TGE" />

==History==
[[File:Hypergate.jpg|thumb|left|250px|A hypergate]]
{{Quote|The hypergates were constructed by our progenitors. They allow immediate egress from one sphere to another, but not in reverse.|Gatemaster [[Beltek'k]].|<ref name="TOR" />}}
These devices were constructed countless millennia ago in a time known to the [[Gree (species)/Legends|Gree]] as "the most ancient and forgotten days." In time, a number of these devices were spread across the space of the [[Gree Enclave/Legends|Gree Enclave]] with dozens once connecting the myriad of Gree worlds.<ref name="TORC" /> In the aftermath of their creation, other forms of personal interplanetary travel became obsolete though starships were still used on occasion, though eventually even the Gree did not understand hypergate technology well.<ref name="TGE" /> On [[Tython/Legends|Tython]], the early [[Je'daii]] [[Tythan]]s discovered the [[Old City (Tython)|Old City]] that had been long ago abandoned and rumors persisted of a working hypergate present in the settlement but none had been discovered.<ref name="DotJ0">[[Star Wars: Dawn of the Jedi 0|''Star Wars: Dawn of the Jedi'' 0]]</ref>

During the [[Galactic War]] between the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and the [[Sith Empire (Post–Great Hyperspace War)|Sith Empire]], the rogue [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] known as the [[Dread Masters]] directed their servant [[Kephess]] to the Gree world of Asation. Once there, the twisted [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshan]] activated the hypergate and allowed countless unknown terrors to ravage the planet. In response, the Gree sent ambassadors to both the Republic and Empire to request aid. A group of [[Spacer/Legends|spacers]] from one faction later traveled to Asation, where they [[Raid on Asation|battled]] the creatures besieging the planet and confronted Kephess, who was ultimately killed. However, the opened hypergate brought a [[Lotek'k|monstrous being]] to the planet, which the spacers had to force back into the hyperspace threshold and remove its hold from the gate, thus defeating it.<ref name="TfB">{{TORcite|type=operation|Terror from Beyond}}</ref> Later, the Dread Masters constructed more hypergates on [[Oricon]], the moon where [[Dread Fortress|their fortress]] was located.<ref name="Oricon">{{TORcite|exp=rothc|type=location|Oricon}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
In the [[1991]] [[West End Games]] supplement ''[[Graveyard of Alderaan]]'', an experimental hypergate was present on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]], where a group of rebels used it to travel between a remnant of the [[Royal Palace of Alderaan/Legends|Aldera Royal Palace]] and the bridge of the [[Alderaanian War Frigate]] ''[[Another Chance]]''. However, when the adventure was reprinted in ''[[Classic Adventures: Volume Two]]'', all reference to the hypergate was removed, and the Rebels boarded the ''Another Chance'' via a [[GAT-12 Skipray Blastboat]].

